### Steps to reproduce
1. Use vue-cli init with TypeScript.
1. Add code to src/components/HelloWorld.vue as below.

```
<script lang="ts">
import Vue, { PropType } from 'vue'

interface Test {
  a: string;
}

export default Vue.extend({
  name: 'HelloWorld',

  props: {
    msg: String,
    test: {
      type: Object as PropType<Test>,
      default: () => ({})
    }
  },

  created () {
    console.log(this.test)
  }
})
</script>
```

### What is expected?
Type errors does not occur.

### What is actually happening?
